<br>
This patch may make things harder, but adding new strategies to mobs as boring as THO is a welcome change.  Having several unavoidable pops during fights is how things should have been done all along.  Now, you don't just stab away at mobs pinned against walls or in corners, you watch and look around wondering when something unexpected will happen.  Secondary tanks will be tanking the new pops as the guild dispatches each one then returns to the main fight.<br>
<br>
Some more complex strategy will be involved.  I can't wait until my guild does some fights like it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Looks like THO is the only fight currently set up this way.  I haven't heard anything about pops during NToV mob fights, although Aary does have attached vindi-style guards now.  Yelinak, AoW, and Tormax, and Dain are all similar encounters from what I've heard and seen, besides some cool trigger mobs.<br>
<br>
Keep up the new ideas Verant!  And screw it if it doesn't work perfectly, you can always change it again!<br>
<br>
Oh and, by the way, give us multi-windowed chat channels next please. :P<br>
<br>
Kahdius Ka`tan<br>
Assassin of Karana<br>
